This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and classification of tweets based on their content. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing social media data. The use of deep learning architectures also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the ethical implications of hate speech on social media. Finally, it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the classification of tweets based on their content.
